description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to recruit a Ventilation manager into our team at University Hospital Southampton Foundation NHS Trust (UHS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Estates Maintenance department has a demonstrable track record in developing staff to enhance personal learning through training and promotional opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is based at Southampton General Hospital &amp; Princess Anne Hospital and does not require travel as part of day-to-day duties (static site), however some training opportunities are provided at off-site facilities. The successful candidates will form part of a large multi-disciplinary team of approximately 50 staff across various disciplines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trust operates a number of Specialist Ventilation systems for areas such as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operating Theatres (Conventional &amp; UCV)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean Rooms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Isolation Facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Decontamination Facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;LEV systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key duties of the role will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaison with projects team &amp; consultants to ensure delivered works meet requirements of industry standards &amp; organisational requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review of Validation &amp; verification documents including overseeing remedial actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivery of Fire Damper Testing program across UHS Buildings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day-to-day management of AHU Filter contract&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical advice with regards to all aspects of Ventilation Maintenance &amp; Testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have suitable relevant experience working with specialised healthcare ventilation installations and have a detailed understanding of their design, operation &amp; compliance with relevant standards/industry guidance including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HTM03-01&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DW144&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS9999:2017&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HBN04-01&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have a solid employment background within the design, commissioning or maintenance of specialist healthcare ventilation and have a proven record of taking pragmatic steps to tackle onsite issues regarding patient safety &amp; compliance with relevant standards. Experience working within a healthcare environment is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will possess the following qualities;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read &amp; interpret engineering drawings and documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good IT Skills, ability to use MS Office &amp; BMS Systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to delivering a robust system to ensure compliance of healthcare ventilation installations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible approach to work depending on needs of team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keenness to develop their skillset and knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to train and develop other team members including apprentices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read &amp; interpret engineering drawings and documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good IT Skills, ability to use MS Office &amp; BMS Systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to delivering a robust system to ensure compliance of healthcare ventilation installations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible approach to work depending on needs of team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keenness to develop their skillset and knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to train and develop other team members including apprentices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest acute teaching Trust’s in England, we can offer learning and development opportunities to help you achieve the career you aspire to. We believe you deserve the best possible surroundings in which to do your job and we want to support you in doing your job to the best of your ability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Trust, we support flexible working and will consider requests taking into account the needs of the service. You’ll have an opportunity to discuss this at interview. Our LiveWell and inspire programme offers opportunities, support and advice, including smoking cessation services, exercise and activity classes, and support for mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UHS employees are able to access a huge range of NHS discounts, are entitled to a minimum of 35 days paid holiday (pro rata) on appointment, can access on-site nursery facilities (subject to availability), and we offer a generous pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT OUR TRUST AND SOUTHAMPTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UHS is rated ‘Good’ by the CQC and in the latest national NHS Staff Survey, we were in the top 10 acute trusts for staff engagement and for staff recommending the hospital as a place to work or receive care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Southampton is an attractive place to live and work situated on the south coast, with an international airport and only an hour on the train from central London. The New Forest National Park and the beaches of the Jurassic coast are also right on our doorstep. The city offers living costs 20% lower than those in London, 13 schools rated outstanding by Ofsted and 13 nearby green spaces to enjoy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ADDITIONAL INFORMATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on Monday, 16th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greg Hansell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Infrastructure Maintenance Manager&lt;/p&gt;
